      "content": "From an economic standpoint, proponents argue that uncontrolled immigration floods the labor market with low-wage competition, which directly depresses wages for native-born, low-skilled workers. By enforcing stricter immigration, the supply of cheap, unauthorized labor is curtailed, allowing domestic workers to command higher wages and maintain economic stability. This controlled environment ensures that the economic benefits of immigration are realized through legal, taxed channels rather than through undercutting local labor standards.",
      "source": "target",
